{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WRRRbSHc1TpbQrb4wGMjGP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01R2s9MzLjwDzz7zesqjMM5i","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n ray create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"RAY CLUSTER CONFIGURATION AUDIT REPORT\nDate: 2026-06-26\nNamespace: ray\nAudit Type: Read-Only (no changes made to cluster)\nAuditor: Automated compliance scan\n\n===============================================================\nCOMPONENT INVENTORY\n===============================================================\n\nDeployments:\n  ray-head    1/1 Ready  (1 replica)\n  ray-worker  1/1 Ready  (1 replica)\n\nPods (all on node karma-2-control-plane):\n  ray-head-5c586c8fd6-9g8gf     Running  IP: 10.244.0.19\n  ray-worker-7d7d685797-2m6mz   Running  IP: 10.244.0.20\n  ray-client                    Running  IP: 10.244.0.21\n\nServices:\n  ray-head  ClusterIP  10.96.186.11  6379/TCP (GCS)\n\nConfigMaps:\n  kube-root-ca.crt  (system-managed, auto-injected)\n\n===============================================================\nWORKER REPLICA COUNT\n===============================================================\nCurrent: 1 replica (spec.replicas=1 on ray-worker Deployment)\nStatus:  1/1 Ready, 1 available\n\n===============================================================\nIMAGE VERSIONS\n===============================================================\nray-head:   rayproject/ray:2.9.0\nray-worker: rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n\nBoth components use the same image tag. Ray 2.9.0 is a pinned\nversion tag (not 'latest').\n\nDEVIATION: Image is referenced by mutable version tag rather\nthan an immutable digest (sha256). The registry could serve a\ndifferent layer set without changing the tag string.\n\n===============================================================\nRESOURCE REQUESTS / LIMITS\n===============================================================\nray-head   container 'ray-head':   resources: {} (NONE SET)\nray-worker container 'ray-worker': resources: {} (NONE SET)\n\nDEVIATION: No CPU or memory requests or limits are defined on\neither Deployment. The Kubernetes scheduler cannot make informed\nplacement decisions and pods may consume unbounded resources,\nrisking node pressure, OOMKill, or workload starvation.\n\n===============================================================\nRAY HEAD STARTUP CONFIGURATION\n===============================================================\nCommand:\n  ray start --head \\\n    --node-ip-address=\\${MY_POD_IP} \\\n    --port=6379 \\\n    --include-dashboard=false \\\n    --num-cpus=0 \\\n    --block\n\nNotable flags:\n  --include-dashboard=false  Dashboard is explicitly DISABLED\n  --num-cpus=0               Head node accepts no compute tasks\n                             (standard best-practice pattern)\n  --port=6379                GCS listening port\n\nEnvironment variables injected:\n  MY_POD_IP   <- status.podIP  (downward API)\n  RAY_NODE_ID <- metadata.uid  (downward API)\n  RAY_RAYLET_PID = 1\n\n===============================================================\nRAY WORKER STARTUP CONFIGURATION\n===============================================================\nCommand:\n  ray start \\\n    --address=ray-head:6379 \\\n    --node-ip-address=\\${MY_POD_IP} \\\n    --num-cpus=1 \\\n    --block\n\nNotable flags:\n  --num-cpus=1  Each worker pod advertises 1 CPU to the scheduler\n  Connects to head via Kubernetes service DNS: ray-head:6379\n\nEnvironment variables injected:\n  MY_POD_IP   <- status.podIP  (downward API)\n  RAY_NODE_ID <- metadata.uid  (downward API)\n  RAY_RAYLET_PID = 1\n\n===============================================================\nSERVICE AND NETWORK EXPOSURE\n===============================================================\nService: ray-head\n  Type:       ClusterIP (internal cluster access only)\n  Cluster IP: 10.96.186.11\n  Port:       6379/TCP  name=gcs  (Global Control Store)\n\n  Dashboard port (8265): NOT present in Service spec\n  External access (NodePort/LoadBalancer/Ingress): NONE\n\nThe Ray dashboard is both disabled at the process level\n(--include-dashboard=false) and absent from the Service.\nDashboard observability is not available in the current state.\n\n===============================================================\nCONFIGMAPS\n===============================================================\nkube-root-ca.crt  (1 key, age ~60s at audit time)\n  System-managed CA cert bundle injected by Kubernetes.\n  No user-created ConfigMaps are present in the namespace.\n\n===============================================================\nDEVIATIONS FROM BASELINE / DEFAULTS\n===============================================================\n[DEV-1] No resource requests or limits on ray-head or ray-worker.\n  Both containers have resources:{} — unbounded resource usage.\n\n[DEV-2] Ray dashboard disabled (--include-dashboard=false) and\n  not exposed on the Service. Default Ray installations expose\n  the dashboard on port 8265.\n\n[DEV-3] All three pods (ray-head, ray-worker, ray-client) are\n  co-located on a single node (karma-2-control-plane). No pod\n  anti-affinity rules are configured, creating a single point\n  of failure if that node becomes unavailable.\n\n[DEV-4] Image referenced by mutable version tag (ray:2.9.0)\n  rather than an immutable content digest.\n\n===============================================================\nCOMPLIANCE NOTES AND RECOMMENDATIONS\n===============================================================\n[HIGH]   DEV-1: Set resource requests and limits on both\n  ray-head and ray-worker containers before the next change\n  window. Without requests, the scheduler cannot guarantee\n  capacity; without limits, runaway processes can impact\n  other namespaces.\n\n[MEDIUM] DEV-4: Pin images by digest (e.g.,\n  rayproject/ray@sha256:<hash>) in Deployment specs to ensure\n  reproducible, tamper-evident deployments.\n\n[MEDIUM] DEV-3: Add pod anti-affinity rules or use multiple\n  nodes to avoid co-location of head and worker. Define a\n  PodDisruptionBudget to protect the cluster during maintenance.\n\n[LOW]    DEV-2: If dashboard observability is required, enable\n  it (remove --include-dashboard=false or set =true) and add\n  port 8265 to the ray-head Service definition.\n\n[LOW]    Add liveness and readiness probes to both Deployments\n  to enable automatic recovery from hung Ray processes.\n\n===============================================================\nAUDIT SUMMARY\n===============================================================\nThe Ray cluster in namespace 'ray' is running with a minimal\nconfiguration: 1 ray-head pod, 1 ray-worker pod (1 CPU each),\nand 1 ray-client pod. Both Deployments use image\nrayproject/ray:2.9.0. No resource requests or limits are set\non any container. The Ray dashboard is explicitly disabled and\nnot exposed via any Service. The ray-head Service exposes only\nGCS port 6379 as ClusterIP (no external access). No user-created\nConfigMaps are present. The primary compliance gap is the\nabsence of resource constraints on both Deployments.\n\nLive cluster state was not modified during this audit.\n\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with audit findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3287,"cache_read_input_tokens":30036,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3287},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98a202a3-133a-48ed-a212-7a7add8602e2","uuid":"896edc77-88ba-4eb9-b837-222b865e4c4b","request_id":"req_011CcRJEre8QAHghoppL1ZcH"}
